Feb 14 2009 	Wonderful service - Great hotel	The Elizabeth Hotel37 Eccleston SquareLondon, EnglandOur family of three adults stayed at The Elizabeth Hotel for three nights from Friday, January 29 until Monday, February 2, 2009. Yes, Monday, February 2, the day of the recent snow storm in London. I had e-mailed several times to the hotel asking questions regarding the accommodations before making a reservation and always received a prompt and courteous reply. I booked a two bedroom, one bathroom (with a bathtub and overhead shower) apartment (Flat 5) and was very pleased with that choice.The Apartment - The apartment was on the top floor of the hotel (the elevator went to one floor below the apartment and the apartment had one flight of stairs inside the entrance door) and had lovely views of the park across the street from both the living room and kitchen windows. One bedroom had one very comfortable double bed, dresser with lots of drawers and a closet to hang clothing. The twin bedroom had two twin beds and a closet also. The living room had one couch and one chair, TV and lots of space. The kitchen was very well equipped with a microwave, surface stove, oven, refrigerator, dishwasher and a washing machine. The furnishings were comfortable and the whole apartment was SPOTLESSLY clean. The hot water took a while to get to the hotel's top floor but it always did and we had plenty of it. The bathroom amenities (shampoo, lotion, bar soap) were replenished daily as well as fresh towels delivered. The Elevator (The LIft) - Yes, it is very small and creaky but it always worked and was appreciated. The Breakfast - Two nicely decorated small rooms where an excellant full English breakfast could be had or cereals, danish rolls, warm croissants and fresh fruit salad (very good) were available. Pots of tea were delivered to your table from smiling staff. The waitstaff did an amazing job serving many people, always with a greeting and a smile in a small amout of space. Yes, one morning we did need to wait five minutes to be seated, but so what !!!! The Location of the Hotel - Perfect for making connections with either the Victoria Bus or Train station. Truly an easy ten minute walk (maxium time) from the station. A taxi cost less than five GBP from the station to the hotel. The blocks around the hotel are a mix of private homes (beautiful old buildings), B &amp; B's, hotels and restaurants. A very walkable area.The Hotel Staff - PERFECT - We arrived very early Friday AM (9:00 AM) with our adult son not feeling well after our overseas flight from the United States. Immediately the receptionist, Monika, found him a clean available room so he could lay down. This help was very much appreciated and during our three day stay I had contact with Ann, Sopie and Simona on different occasions and each one was very professional and helpful. Extra service always with a smile. From help with ordering our dinner to be delivered one evening using the lounge computer, supplying us with cold bottled water, giving accurate directions and to making arrangements ahead of time for our private taxi to pick us up at 5:30 AM on our morning of departure (THE snow day) - Everything was great customer service.The Cost - Very reasonable considering London is a very expensive city. So, YES, I would stay there again and hopefully will get a chance to.	
